             Collins. I was present on the 22nd of December, 1818, at St. Matthew, Bethnal Green, when he married 
               
                  <persName id="t18220417-121-victim1163" type="victimName">
                     Elizabeth 
                     Mason
                  <interp inst="t18220417-121-victim1163" type="surname" value="Mason"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-121-victim1163" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220417-121-victim1163" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            . I had known her for six months previous. She was single - I saw her in Court to day - she had 500 l. or 600 l. They had one child, which is now about eighteen months old. My signature is to the register.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. PHILLIPS. Q. Are you sure she was single before - A. She passed as such.</p>
               <p>
            
